88. Memorandum From the President’s Military Assistant (Haig) to the President’s Assistant
                    for National Security Affairs (Kissinger)Source:
                        National Archives, Nixon Presidential Materials, NSC Files, Staff Files—Staff Memos, Box 1050, Lynn, Laurence E., Jr. Secret; Sensitive;
                        Eyes Only. Kissinger initialed the
                        memorandum, indicating that he saw it.
